Comment:
I absolutely love 3rd Wave Cafe! The coffee is always top-notch, the ambiance is perfect, and the staff is friendly. It's a great spot to relax, catch up on work, or meet with friends. However, there is one major issue that needs addressing‚Äîthe washroom situation.

There is only one washroom for both men and women, and unfortunately, it's frequently occupied by staff members, either from 3rd Wave Cafe or from Crossword. As a regular customer, I've had to wait 20 to 30 minutes just to use the washroom on several occasions. Even others customers are always waiting to use the washroom. It's incredibly frustrating, especially when you're in a rush or just need a quick break.

I feel that the staff should be mindful of the fact that there's only one washroom and avoid prolonged usage, so paying customers aren't left waiting for extended periods. I hope management addresses this issue because, other than this, the cafe is perfect!

This is my go to place as it is very close to my house, this place has some energy and makes me very productive at my work, I sit and read a lot here and self educate myself. The staff here is very caring and also give the best service. Ramesh and Deepa are stand outs always welcoming and providing the best coffee to keep my day going

I had a truly remarkable experience at this place! I decided to let the staff surprise me with a coffee of their choice, even if it was off the menu, as long as they felt it was the perfect pick. Gaurav Singh, who was behind the counter, suggested a coffee and without hesitation kindly offered to alter it or change the drink if it didn‚Äôt reach that mark of my liking. After trying it, I felt it wasn‚Äôt quite to my taste.. I asked him to alter that drink to my liking , I tested his skills, and he adjusted the coffee perfectly, even providing a small sample to ensure it matched what I wanted. After my thumbs-up approval, he made the final drink, which I absolutely loved.
The attention to detail and dedication to customer satisfaction really impressed me. A special shout-out to Harsh Pandey as well, who delivered the coffee with a warm smile, making the entire experience even more enjoyable. I truly appreciated the effort they put in to ensure I was happy with my drink!

Comment:
What's common between a frustrated IT employee's mood and Bengaluru's weather ?
Both are unpredictable.
We had to visit this outlet of "third wave coffee" due to unexpected rains while we were shopping at MG Road.
The outlet appears to be small, but it actually consists of a ground floor with few tables, a mirror stuck staircase takes us to a spacious yet clumsy 1st floor where a lot of tables are put together to accommodate lots of people

We ordered a cinnamon roll since we had already finished our lunch and we wanted a shelter till the rain stopped. 
Found a table at the corner of the first floor and waited for our order.
After an eternity,  we got our order with one fork and one butter knife, the staff didn't even bother to ask if we needed another fork, and we didn't bother to disturb him since all the staff looked already disturbed due the large crowd.

And the rain did stop too, so we ate the cinnamon roll with our bare hands in a hurry so that we could continue our shopping.
So our purpose was solved and the dessert was tasty too but they can reduce one or two tables so that it feels bit comfortable and you wouldn't be hearing the conversation that's happening on the table next to you.

The ambiance is cozy and ideal for working, with plenty of seating and a relaxed vibe. Their coffee menu is top-notch, featuring everything from classic brews to more experimental options. Whether you're a coffee connoisseur or just looking for a great place to chill, this spot won't disappoint!

This is purely related to my experience which doesn't include either Coffee or Food. Hope the owners read it.

It was a terrible experience for us as I was already in the Coffee shop waiting for my friend yesterday. While i was waiting, my friend was denied an entry by the security 'on the main road' stating there is no parking. When my friend called to update me, the security i spoke was rude and stated the coffee shop has parking only to park 2 cars and there are other empty slots (majority belong to other establishments it seems). This was on Wednesday at 11am and there are hardly any customers.

So, how do you expect customers to visit your coffee shop when they are being chased away?
The staff are just helpless and try to do nothing
The Wifi that I did try to connect never sent an OTP

Please fix your core problems or set expectations that there is no parking (as Varthur main road is narrow and there are no designated parking slots as they are in places like Jaya Nagar) and then you will be able to do some business. Else you may shut shop soon.

Comment:
Edited Review :- I recently visited Third Wave Coffee Roasters in Andheri West and had a delightful experience. The ambiance is cozy yet modern, with warm lighting and comfortable seating that makes it perfect for both casual meet-ups or focused work sessions. The cafe offers an impressive selection of coffee, particularly their single-origin brews, which are freshly roasted and full of flavor. I opted for their pour-over, which was brewed to perfection, highlighting the rich, nuanced notes of the beans.

The staff is knowledgeable and attentive, happy to walk you through the different brewing methods and flavor profiles. They also offer a variety of snacks and light bites that pair well with the coffee, making it an ideal spot for breakfast or a midday break.

Overall, Third Wave Coffee Roasters in Andheri West is a good spot for your regular coffee or anyone looking for a quiet and stylish place to relax or work.

We didn‚Äôt order food‚Ä¶ only coffees, but they were excellent!!! Best coffee I had in India during my 2-week stay. I would say, this cafe was better than Starbucks even ü§£
If you‚Äôre European in Bengaluru and are missing some of local cafes - definitely visit!!! There is also some exotic flavour- I had a hot salted latte and it had some‚Ä¶ aniseed (?) added. But wonderful atmosphere and staff, great space to meet with friends! Clean bathroom, and on the walls some funny pictures and quotations. Good fun!

I had the pleasure of visiting Third Wave Coffee, Golf Course Road recently, and I must say, the barista staff truly exceeded my expectations. From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with warm smiles and genuine enthusiasm. The team here knows how to make you feel welcome, even during busy hours. Despite the steady stream of customers, they remained calm, composed, and attentive, making sure each guest received personalized service.

What impressed me most was their expertise and attention to detail. Each drink was carefully crafted, and it was clear that the baristas take pride in their skills. My latte was not only perfectly brewed with just the right balance of rich espresso and creamy milk, but it was also beautifully presented with latte art that added an extra touch of charm. It's evident that they put thought and care into every cup, no matter how simple or complex the order.

Beyond their technical skills, the baristas were more than willing to offer recommendations and answer questions about their menu, demonstrating a genuine passion for coffee. They even took the time to explain the origins of the beans they use, which made the experience feel even more special.

Overall, the baristas at TWC especially Anoop, Gaurav and all the other staff deliver not just great coffee, but also an exceptional customer experience. Their friendly demeanor, professional service, and evident love for their craft make this place a standout in the local coffee scene. I'll definitely be returning soon!

(Translated by Google) Nice place and nothing more. We ordered a cold press that was not tasty, and a chocolate cake that wasn't bad. We asked for lactose-free milk and there was none. The service is relatively slow and we had to wait more than 20 minutes until the coffee arrived. We bought beans (540 rupees for 350 grams) and asked to grind them into black coffee - and they couldn't grind them fine enough... although they certainly tried. A beautifully decorated place and there is excellent Wi-Fi. All in all a nice experience and probably the best coffee in the area but certainly not third wave as we know from developed countries. Relatively very expensive - is it justified you decide for yourself.

Comment:
I am a regular to this outlet, but offlate disappointment is creepung in
The vibe coming from this outlet is like a normal non branded neighbourhood coffee shop, mainly because of their policies....
Parking is a nuisance here, they don't have their own provision for parking...
Unlike their other esteemed competitor, they are very rigid and are not willing to give anything extra to their regular customers... Also all the other coffee shops in the neighbourhood are having good provision for parking...
I am addicted to coffee and I love working from Cafe but unfortunately, need to drop Third wave from my list...
The last point I want to add is that by service it implies the staff at the outlet is responsible but many time the staff need's to work within the perimeter set by management. The staff at the outlet are great but the service is lacking as their hands are tied..
My message is towards the management, please buckle up. The locality in which this outlet is located is having lots of option, so customer can very well afford to ignore you

Comment: Nice ice latte with almond milk and amazing service by Sanjay

We tried the English cucumber and cream cheese bagel and iced latte here. The food, ambience and service were all really good. The coffee really had an authentic taste and was very effective. We were really tired and sleepy and the coffee hit just the right spot. It cured us in minutes. If you are visiting, then do install their app which gives you some offers like 100 rupees off on 1st order, points / rewards on orders etc. You can also use upto 200 Flipkart coins on an order here however, that option was not working for us due to some technical issues from their end (also note that this offer cannot be clubbed with other offers). It is worth mentioning that this is more suitable for people who like European food as their menu and food taste caters to that palate with items like cinnamon roll, bagel, croissant etc. The coffee was also bitter unlike the usual sugar induced version we find at local vendors. No doubt they serve top quality food, it is just that the food they serve may be an acquired taste for some people. And this place is also on the expensive side, so if you are on a budget you might want to skip this.
Staff is very courteous and friendly :)

Our last visit to this cafe was a bit disappointing as we ordered mexican paneer sandwich and it was too spicy and we weren't informed about it. It was too spicy compared to normal spicy food we eat and upon informing it to the cashier he was a bit casual about it saying that it's normally this spicy everytime!

I would suggest marking it on the menu so that people come to know about it and avoid from ordering it as it might lead to wastage of food!
